# Publish, verify, DM

## Step

Resolved when the wiki build on flagg (`bun run build`, retry once on
transient exit 1) picks up the page,
`https://brain.joelclaw.com/joelclaw/resources/memory-system/` returns HTTP
200 (exact URL check, never share unverified), and Joel gets the link via
`joelclaw notify send`. Close the brief (`status: "done"`) if this is the
last open step.

## Result (2026-07-17)

Published. First build failed for a real (not transient) reason: two
newly-registered observer brain pages carried unescaped `{...}` in prose,
and `observer/tasks/tick-summary-render` threw `severity is not defined`
at prerender. Fixed both files (observer `2e768c2b`, promoted to release),
rebuilt clean (exit 0). Verified 200 on the exact URLs:
`/joelclaw/resources/memory-system/`, `/observer/tasks/neat-memory-beat/`
(observer root's first live page), and the periphery survey. Link DM'd to
Joel. Note: the page rendered from the working tree; its provenance commit
stamp fills in on the next build after this commit.
